                <h2>Andhra Pradesh: The Legend of Lord Venkateswara (Tirupati)</h2>
                <p>The legend of Lord Venkateswara, also known as Balaji, is steeped in devotion and divine intervention. According to mythology, Lord Vishnu descended to Earth in the form of Venkateswara during the Kali Yuga to guide humanity. He resided on the sacred Tirumala hills in Andhra Pradesh. The story highlights his marriage to Princess Padmavati, daughter of King Akasaraja, in a celestial ceremony attended by gods and sages. The Tirupati Temple, one of the world's wealthiest temples, is a center of devotion where millions of devotees come to seek blessings, believing that darshan of Lord Venkateswara absolves their sins and bestows prosperity.</p>
