                <h2>Arunachal Pradesh: The Myth of Donyi-Polo (Sun and Moon)</h2>
                <p>In Arunachal Pradesh, the tribal faith revolves around Donyi (the Sun) and Polo (the Moon). These celestial entities symbolize balance and harmony in life. Donyi represents warmth, vitality, and life-giving energy, while Polo embodies coolness and serenity. The indigenous tribes hold rituals and festivals to honor these deities, seeking their blessings for peace, fertility, and prosperity. The philosophy of Donyi-Polo emphasizes living in harmony with nature and respecting the cosmic balance.</p>
