                <h2>Assam: The Legend of Kamakhya Temple</h2>
                <p>The Kamakhya Temple, perched on the Nilachal Hill in Assam, is one of India's most revered Shakti Peethas. According to legend, this is where the womb and genitalia of Goddess Sati fell when Lord Shiva carried her charred body across the universe after her self-immolation. The temple uniquely celebrates the goddess's menstrual cycle as a symbol of fertility and regeneration. The annual Ambubachi Mela draws thousands of devotees, signifying the goddess's sacred power of creation.</p>
