                <h2>Bihar: The Birth of Sita (Sitamarhi)</h2>
                <p>Sitamarhi in Bihar is believed to be the birthplace of Sita, the heroine of the Ramayana. The legend narrates that King Janaka discovered Sita while plowing a field, symbolizing her divine origin and purity. The discovery also underscores the themes of fertility and divine intervention. Sitamarhi remains a sacred site where devotees pay homage to Sita’s virtuousness and strength, reflecting her role as an ideal woman in Indian culture.</p>
