                <p>Maa Danteshwari, an incarnation of Goddess Shakti, is deeply revered in Chhattisgarh. The Danteshwari Temple in Dantewada, one of the 52 Shakti Peethas, marks the spot where her tooth fell when Lord Shiva carried her body. The temple is a significant pilgrimage site, especially during the Dussehra festival. The legend symbolizes unwavering devotion and the protection offered by the divine mother.</p>
