                <p>According to mythology, Lord Parshuram, an avatar of Vishnu, reclaimed the land of Goa from the sea by shooting an arrow into the Arabian Sea. The waters receded, revealing the land that became Goa. This act of divine creation highlights Goa's spiritual significance and prosperity. The legend also reflects the cultural synthesis of myth and geography that defines the region.</p>
