                <h2>Meghalaya: The Folklore of Ka Likai Falls</h2>
                <p>Ka Likai Falls, one of the tallest waterfalls in India, is tied to a tragic tale of grief. According to folklore, Likai was a widow who remarried to provide for her child. However, her jealous husband killed the child and served the remains as a meal to Likai. Upon discovering the horrific truth, Likai, overcome by despair, leaped to her death from the cliffs near the falls. The falls are a symbol of sorrow and serve as a poignant reminder of human tragedy. Visitors often reflect on the story while marveling at the breathtaking beauty of the falls.</p>
