                <p>Sohni Mahiwal is a legendary Punjabi love story of passion and sacrifice. Sohni, a potter’s daughter, secretly met her lover Mahiwal, a herdsman, across the Chenab River using an earthen pot to float. One fateful night, her jealous sister-in-law replaced the pot with an unbaked one, which dissolved midstream, leading to Sohni’s tragic drowning. Mahiwal jumped in to save her, and both perished. This tale immortalizes their love and inspires countless retellings in Punjabi folklore, poetry, and art.</p>
