                <p>The Madurai Meenakshi Temple is a masterpiece of Dravidian architecture and a center of devotion. The temple celebrates the divine marriage of Goddess Meenakshi (an incarnation of Parvati) and Lord Sundareswarar (Shiva). According to legend, Meenakshi was born with three breasts, and it was prophesied that the extra breast would vanish when she met her future husband. When she encountered Shiva, the prophecy came true. The temple is a symbol of love, divine power, and artistic brilliance, attracting millions of devotees and tourists annually.
